It is the 17th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}, preceded by {{ill|Kibou|ja|己卯}} and followed by {{ill|Shinshi|ja|辛巳}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|lt=Yin Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} symbol {{ill|Kou|ja|庚}} represents yang {{ill|Metal|ja|金}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} symbol {{ill|Dragon|ja|辰}} represents yang {{ill|Earth|ja|土}}, establishing a generating relationship ({{ill|Mutual Generation|ja|五行思想#相生（そうじょう）|lt=Mutual Generation|lt_ja=相生}}) (i.e. Earth generates Metal).

== {{ill|Years of Koushin|ja|庚辰の年}} ==
A year in the {{ill|Western calendar|ja|西暦}} that leaves a remainder of 20 when divided by 60 is a year of {{ill|Koushin|ja|庚辰}} ({{ill|year|ja|年}}).
